14
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Andy have a boo-boo tummy.

15
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Would you rather me say,

16
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:39,000
hey guys, my irritable bowel syndrome is flaring up.

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Crazy diarrhea happening right now.

18
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Because things can get real adult real fast.

19
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
You are also on record as saying,

20
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
whittle-iddle, footy-woody's, num-nums, jammies,

21
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
make boom-boom, widdicawess, and woad-eye-wind.

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Do I sometimes replace r's with w's?

23
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Do I sometimes repeat a word to get my point across?

24
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Well, if I do, Andy, sorry.

25
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
You can't be a baby in the office.

26
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
It makes me look like I hire babies.

27
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Well, if we are complaining,

28
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,000
a lot of people think your Elvis voice is annoying.

29
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Okay, who said that?

30
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Just people.

31
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
For the record, I think it is pretty fantastic.

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Well, thank you.

33
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Thank you a lot.

34
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,000
And for what it is worth, I think your baby voice is top.

35
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Thank you, Mr. Elvis.

36
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
You are welcome, by the way.

37
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:45,640
MUSIC

38
